reinforce so many things that

00:03:25.390 --> 00:03:27.850 align:middle line:10%
getting older I've
learned to understand,

00:03:27.850 --> 00:03:33.160 align:middle line:10%
it becomes just so important
that we take a good look

00:03:33.160 --> 00:03:37.420 align:middle line:10%
at how critical this is
and what Box 12 represented

00:03:37.420 --> 00:03:40.550 align:middle line:10%
and what it really means
to-- like a call to action.

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:43.280 align:middle line:84%
It's why I really wanted to
get on this show, George.

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:47.020 align:middle line:84%
We need to have a call to
action about the value we

00:03:47.020 --> 00:03:49.540 align:middle line:84%
place upon this thing
that we call death.

00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:52.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do you
stay so upbeat, so

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:55.990 align:middle line:84%
positive with all these
experiences that happened?

00:03:55.990 --> 00:03:58.720 align:middle line:84%
>>BRINKLEY: Well, everybody
has a purpose, George.

00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:00.280 align:middle line:90%
I'm lucky enough to know mine.

00:04:00.280 --> 00:04:05.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I learned it in
1975 as a jackass to see

00:04:05.920 --> 00:04:07.940 align:middle line:90%
